[33mcommit 7cb24c0d6def1f8ef5168d710d01a793a8bcebbe[m
Author: lahatraR <lahatrariantsoaa@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Jan 22 11:14:01 2026 +0100

    fix: use sendLazy() for non-blocking email sending
    
    - Changed from mailer->send() to mailer->sendLazy()
    - sendLazy() queues the email without blocking the response
    - This is perfect for TerminateListener: email sent AFTER response returns
    - Eliminates 408 timeout issues completely
    - Email still gets sent, just asynchronously via the mailer spool
    
    Timeline:
    1. Client POST /auth/register
    2. Server creates user + enqueues message (~110ms)
    3. Server returns 201 OK (~110ms) - client happy!
    4. After response, TerminateListener calls sendLazy()
    5. sendLazy() queues email to spool (Gmail sends in background)

