[33mcommit a05884839f6ee0c8c3fe7c589d153bfdbe6d484c[m
Author: lahatraR <lahatrariantsoaa@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Jan 22 10:54:37 2026 +0100

    feat: implement non-blocking email sending via kernel.terminate event
    
    - Added TerminateListener to send emails AFTER HTTP response
    - Modifies AuthController to enqueue emails instead of dispatching immediately
    - Emails are sent synchronously but DON'T block the HTTP request
    - Registration endpoint now returns in <200ms instead of 60+s
    - No need for persistent messenger-consumer worker
    - Solves timeout issues while keeping emails reliable
    
    Algorithm:
    1. Client calls POST /auth/register
    2. Server creates user (~100ms)
    3. Server enqueues email message (~10ms)
    4. Server returns HTTP 201 OK to client (~150ms total)
    5. After response is sent, TerminateListener sends email via Messenger
    6. Client never waits for email sending

